comments.body: Sapsucker observed for a couple minutes feeding in a pepper tree, and then it flew to a jacaranda tree. Bird had a red throat outlined with black bib and distinct face lines of white. Had a red crown and nape, with a red wash to the cheeks. The red also bled into the bib a bit on the sides of throat. I took a crappy iPhone pic, which I uploaded. Went back with a camera but couldn’t refind the bird. Hopefully it sticks and I can get better documentation. The bird is in the center of the photograph on the large branch of the pepper tree. I have considerable experience observing hybrids of these two species in northeastern California and southern Oregon.
